The course provides students with knowledge and understanding of information architecture as a developing field and introduces the basic approaches and principles in organizing information.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to give an overview of different approaches and concepts of information architecture and understandings in organizing information. Through reading texts and participating in discussions, students learn about the history, principles, theories and various practical approaches of information architecture.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course, students are able: - to formulate and analyze the principles of information architecture in different information environments; - understand and critically analyze information organization systems (taxonomy, etc.); - apply the principles of information architecture in real information environments; - to discuss what is included in the concept of information architecture and other basic concepts in the field; - create and describe and make recommendations for the application of information architecture principles, especially when organizing web information.
